question: Henry has 85 square meters of raspberry field. There are 27 raspberrys per square meter. Henry can harvest his raspberrys every 12 months. How many raspberrys can Henry harvest within a year?
answer:
Henry has 27*85= <<27*85=2295>>2295 raspberrys on his field.
Henry can harvest his raspberrys 12 / 12 = <<12/12=1>>1 times per year
Therefore Henry can harvest 2295*1 = <<2295*1=2295>>2295 raspberrys per year.
#### 2295
